As they undertake their arduous climb, their egos and frayed nerves begin to get in the way of staying together as a team. The shared responsibility of lugging along a 45-kg accessory certainly does not help their cause. Will they come together before it’s too late?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 3
programme.desc: While the team begins to come together as one, awareness dawns on how different their individual attitudes and confidence levels are. While one of them, realizes they cannot complete the task and prepares to descend, another questions if her pace is setting everyone back. Keeping her on and walking at her pace would mean sacrificing watching the prized sunrise at the summit. Are they ready to give up on that ? They are getting beaten down, but they must go on. Will they make it before sunrise?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 4
programme.desc: A sea of clouds and a magical sunrise await the team at the summit. With the team’s belief in themselves and each other reinforced, they think about what it took to overcome their obstacles. The moment is especially poignant for one member who pays tribute to the memory of his late son and spends a quiet moment in remembrance of him. As each of them grapple with the emotions that overtake them on the summit, Joe De Sena reminds them that reaching the summit is not the end of their journey – its’s only the beginning. Where will the Spartan spirit take them next?

programme.title: Inside Kilian Jornet

This documentary follows Jornet through an intense 10-day tour of 10 cities around the world, allowing the public to see, for the first time, everything that goes on around the professional athlete, and revealing his lesser-known, uninhibited side. Between presentations, interviews, and brand commitments, and with only a few hours' sleep, the athlete reflects on a year marked by injuries his search for the balance between competition and personal projects and the arrival of his first daughter.

programme.title: MessiCirque

We will accompany the creators, artists and Messi on a trip from Montreal to Barcelona and discover a story about dreams that come true. Finally contemplating a return to civilisation, and his imminent death, Jesus happens upon a troubled family dealing with a much more earthly problem: the young son being desperate to leave the familial home against his father’s wishes, in search of the big city. Amid this family struggle we see Jesus wrestling not only with Satan, but also with his own faith.

But Maria's mother, devout Conchita, is disturbed at the idea that prehistoric savages could have created such magnificent art. The Catholic Church sees this as an attack on Biblical truth. And Carthailac, the leading prehistorian, condemns Marcelino and his discovery as fakes. The family is thrown into crisis and the cave locked up. It takes all their love for each other to find a way through to redemption and recognition.

Over the coming days, the emigrants must face the scourges of hunger, thirst and their own lack of faith in each other’s instincts for survival. When a Native American wanderer crosses their path, the emigrants are torn between their trust in a guide who has proven himself unreliable and a man who has always been seen as the natural enemy.

All goes well until a mistake forces these first-time thieves into a last-minute escapade.

Jackson, Jessica Alba and Sophie Turner, Barely Lethal is the unmissable action comedy that shows just how hard surviving high school really is!

As the population grows, space becomes scarce and only the rich and powerful can stay, dumping the poor and orphaned of Skyark to the abandoned earth. Among them is one boy, Rags, the son of a fallen commander who is determined to save his fellow orphans and exiles. The clock is ticking in this exhilarating race against time. Will justice be served or will there be two more bodies to add to the crime toll of the city?
